link: Seiichi Manyama, Table of n, a(n) for n = -1..10000
Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Rogers-Ramanujan Continued Fraction
formula: Expansion of (eta(q) / eta(q^5))^6 in powers of q.
G.f. A(x) satisfies: 0 = f(A(x), A(x^2)) where f(u, v) = u*v * (u*v + 125) - (u+v) * (u^2 - 13 * u*v + v^2).
a(n) = A229793(n) - A078905(n) for n > 0. - _Seiichi Manyama_, Jan 01 2017
mathematica: a[ n_] := SeriesCoefficient[ 1/q (QPochhammer[ q] / QPochhammer[ q^5])^6, {q, 0, n}]; (* _Michael Somos_, May 22 2013 *)
program: (PARI) {a(n) = my(A); if( n<-1, 0, n++; A = x * O(x^n); polcoeff( (eta(x + A) / eta(x^5 + A))^6, n))};
